cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about a neural language model that learns to discover word-like units in unsegmented character sequences and how these words fit together to form sentences. It also conditions the model on visual context to ground the meanings of words in non-linguistic modalities. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of visual context implies that it could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper proposes a new model, which could make it relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
